events.name: New York Knicks at Charlotte Hornets

headlines.description: — Miles Bridges scored 24 points on some high-flying dunks and athletic spin moves, point guard LaMelo Ball had a career-high 17 rebounds to go with 12 points, nine assists and five steals, and the Charlotte Hornets erased an early 16-point deficit to...
headlines.shortLinkText: Bridges, Ball lead Hornets past Walker, Knicks 104-96

headlines.description: — When the Milwaukee Bucks scratched Giannis Antetokounmpo 90 minutes before the tipoff, Boston coach Ime Udoka worried that his team would expect an easy night against the rest of the defending NBA champions.
headlines.shortLinkText: With Giannis scratched, Celtics beat Bucks 122-113 in OT

headlines.description: — Darius Garland tied his season high with 21 points and rookie power forward Evan Mobley had 16 points and seven rebounds, leading the Cleveland Cavaliers to a 98-78 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Garland scores 21 points, Cavaliers rout Pistons 98-78

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Devin Booker and Jae Crowder scored 17 points each, Chris Paul added 15 points and 12 assists as the Phoenix Suns dominated the Memphis Grizzlies 119-94 on Friday night for their seventh straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker, Paul, Crowder help Suns dominate Grizzlies, 119-94

events.name: Brooklyn Nets at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — With James Harden and Kevin Durant both hitting clutch shots, the Brooklyn Nets were able to get away with blowing a 21-point second-half lead on the road.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harden has 39 points, 12 assists, Nets top Pelicans 120-112

events.name: Sacramento Kings at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Lu Dort stole the ball from De’Aaron Fox, then quickly dribbled down the court and made a contested layup in traffic with 1.7 seconds left to give the Oklahoma City Thunder a 105-103 victory over the Sacramento Kings on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dort's late layup gives Thunder comeback win over Kings

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Kristaps Porzingis scored a season-high 32 points, Luka Doncic had 32 points, 15 assists and 12 rebounds and the Dallas Mavericks routed the San Antonio Spurs 123-109 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Porzingis, Doncic lead Mavericks in rout over Spurs, 123-109

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 22 points, 19 rebounds and 10 assists in his return from a one-game suspension, posting his second triple-double of the season to lead the Denver Nuggets to a 105-96 win over the struggling Atlanta Hawks on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic's triple-double leads Nuggets past Hawks 105-96

events.name: Chicago Bulls at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry put on quite a show for his old college coach from Davidson.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry scores 40 points as Warriors beat Bulls 119-93

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns scored 18 of his 29 points during Minnesota's dominant third quarter, and the Timberwolves snapped their six-game losing streak with a 107-83 victory over the Los Angeles Lakers on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Towns, Wolves thrash Lakers 107-83 to snap 6-game skid
